Priya Baghel
PaXton Global IT is looking for

1.POSITION: Lead Cloud Architect
No.of Position:2
Exp.-: 7years
Shift Timings- 1-10PM IST/2-11PM IST
Work Location:Mumbai and Noida
About the client: The client is a leader in providing Broadcast tools and services including Playout,
Postproduction, OTT & Content Supply Chain in India. They are looking at creating a platform on the
cloud with their existing services and tools and expanding the same into the newer age features

Role Summary:
You will play a pivotal role in architecting and leading the development of cloud-based platforms that empower our clients to deliver high-quality content to audiences worldwide.
You will work closely with cross-functional teams, drive innovation,
and ensure the scalability, security, and performance of our cloud solutions.

Responsibilities:
• Lead various teams to work together technically to achieve the vision
• Cloud Architecture: Design, develop, and maintain scalable and reliable cloud-based
architectures that meet the evolving needs of our broadcast technology solutions.
• Platform Development: Lead the development and implementation of cloud-based
platforms, collaborating with engineering teams to ensure successful execution.
• Strategic Planning: Collaborate with senior management to define the cloud architecture
roadmap, aligning it with the company's strategic objectives.
• Technical Leadership: Provide guidance and mentorship to cloud engineering teams,
ensuring best practices, and fostering a culture of excellence.
• Performance Optimization: Continuously optimize cloud infrastructure for cost-efficiency,
performance, and reliability.
• Security: Implement and oversee robust security measures to safeguard data and systems.
• Compliance: Ensure that cloud solutions adhere to industry standards and compliance
requirements.
• Vendor Management: Evaluate and manage relationships with cloud service providers,
making informed recommendations for technology adoption.
• Documentation: Create comprehensive documentation for cloud architectures and
processes.
• Technical Evaluation: Stay updated with the latest cloud technologies and evaluate their
applicability to enhance our solutions.

Qualifications:
• A minimum of 7 years of experience in cloud architecture, with a proven track record of
architecting and implementing cloud-based solutions.
• Strong expertise in leading cloud platforms such as AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud Platform.
• Proficiency in infrastructure as code (IAC) and automation tools (e.g., Terraform, Ansible).
• Experience with containerization and orchestration technologies (e.g., Docker, Kubernetes).
• Deep knowledge of network architecture, security, and compliance in cloud environments.
• Strong leadership and team collaboration skills.
• Excellent communication skills, with the ability to convey complex technical concepts to
non-technical stakeholders.
• Relevant certifications (e.g., AWS Certified Solutions Architect, Azure Solutions Architect) are
a plus.
• Experience & passion for broadcast tech
Email your profile in word format with Sub Line : Lead Cloud Architect | Name | Total Exp |
to erp_ps03@outlook.com

Engenheiro DevOps Azure

Responsabilidades e atribuições:
Como parte do atual processo de migração de self-hosted GitHub Enterprise para GitHub Clould, esse projeto vai implementar GitHub Actions para melhorar nosso desenvolvimento e processos de implementação.
• Configurar e habilitar GitHub Actions para produção.
• Desenvolver plano para migrar lista de pipelines definidos do Octopus Deploy para o GitHub Actions.
• Desenvolver documentação em como usar as novas GitHub Actions implementadas de forma eficiente.
• Identificar possíveis problemas relacionados a migração do Octopus Deploy para GitHub Actions e desenhar estratégias para mitigar.
• Desenvolver um plano de reversão em caso de problemas imprevistos durante a transição.
• Definir critério de testes e procedimentos para configurar Github Actions.
• Implementar um processo de revisão para garantir que as configurações de GitHub Actions estão alinhadas com boas práticas.

Requisitos e qualificações:
• Conhecimento avançado em GitHub e Github Actions.
• Experiência anterior em implementação de GitHub é essencial.
• Preferível conhecimento do GitHub Azure DevOps e Octopus Deploy.
• Inglês fluente

100% remoto

🚀 Sobre a Transfeera

A Transfeera nasceu em 2017 com o objetivo de simplificar a relação das empresas com a rotina de pagamentos, que por muitos anos foi complicada. Através da escuta ativa dos nossos clientes e acompanhamento dos avanços tecnológicos do setor, trabalhamos para ser a melhor e mais segura ponte entre as empresas e a infraestrutura de pagamentos.

Se você acredita que construir pontes entre os que precisam de uma solução e os que oferecem o melhor produto é o caminho para revolucionar o mercado financeiro e construir um futuro sem burocracias e letras miúdas, então você também é Transfeera. Vem com a gente? 🚀

- Vaga Engineering Manager Payments: https://bit.ly/TransfeeraEngineeringManager

- A posição é full-remote, com contrato CLT + benefícios;
